{
  "video_id": "mjDjbJJlqZ0",
  "title": "Alex Steffen: The shareable future of cities",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 15260.0,
      "end_time": 17259.0,
      "text": "Climate change is already a heavy topic,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 17260.0,
      "end_time": 19260.0,
      "text": "and it&#39;s getting heavier"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19260.0,
      "end_time": 21260.0,
      "text": "because we&#39;re understanding"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 21260.0,
      "end_time": 23260.0,
      "text": "that we need to do more than we are."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 23260.0,
      "end_time": 25260.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re understanding, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 25260.0,
      "end_time": 27260.0,
      "text": "that those of us who live in the developed world"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27260.0,
      "end_time": 30260.0,
      "text": "need to be really pushing towards eliminating our emissions."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 30260.0,
      "end_time": 33260.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s, to put it mildly, not what&#39;s on the table now."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 33260.0,
      "end_time": 35260.0,
      "text": "And it tends to feel a little overwhelming"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 35260.0,
      "end_time": 38260.0,
      "text": "when we look at what is there in reality today"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38260.0,
      "end_time": 41260.0,
      "text": "and the magnitude of the problem that we face."
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41260.0,
      "end_time": 44260.0,
      "text": "And when we have overwhelming problems in front of us,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44260.0,
      "end_time": 47260.0,
      "text": "we tend to seek simple answers."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 47260.0,
      "end_time": 50260.0,
      "text": "And I think this is what we&#39;ve done with climate change."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 50260.0,
      "end_time": 52260.0,
      "text": "We look at where the emissions are coming from --"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 52260.0,
      "end_time": 55260.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re coming out of our tailpipes and smokestacks and so forth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 55260.0,
      "end_time": 57260.0,
      "text": "and we say, okay, well the problem is"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 57260.0,
      "end_time": 59260.0,
      "text": "that they&#39;re coming out of fossil fuels that we&#39;re burning,"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59260.0,
      "end_time": 62260.0,
      "text": "so therefore, the answer must be"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 62260.0,
      "end_time": 65259.0,
      "text": "to replace those fossil fuels with clean sources of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 65260.00000000001,
      "end_time": 68260.0,
      "text": "And while, of course, we do need clean energy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 68260.0,
      "end_time": 70260.0,
      "text": "I would put to you that it&#39;s possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 70260.0,
      "end_time": 72260.0,
      "text": "that by looking at climate change"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72260.0,
      "end_time": 74260.0,
      "text": "as a clean energy generation problem,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 74260.0,
      "end_time": 76260.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re in fact setting ourselves up"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 76260.0,
      "end_time": 78260.0,
      "text": "not to solve it."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 78260.0,
      "end_time": 80260.0,
      "text": "And the reason why"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 80260.0,
      "end_time": 82260.0,
      "text": "is that we live on a planet"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 82260.0,
      "end_time": 84260.0,
      "text": "that is rapidly urbanizing."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 84260.0,
      "end_time": 86260.0,
      "text": "That shouldn&#39;t be news to any of us."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 86260.0,
      "end_time": 88260.0,
      "text": "However, it&#39;s hard sometimes"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88260.0,
      "end_time": 91260.0,
      "text": "to remember the extent of that urbanization."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 91260.0,
      "end_time": 93260.0,
      "text": "By mid-century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 93260.0,
      "end_time": 96260.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to have about eight billion -- perhaps more -- people"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 96260.0,
      "end_time": 99260.0,
      "text": "living in cities or within a day&#39;s travel of one."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 99260.0,
      "end_time": 102260.0,
      "text": "We will be an overwhelmingly urban species."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 102260.0,
      "end_time": 104260.0,
      "text": "In order to provide"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 104260.0,
      "end_time": 106260.0,
      "text": "the kind of energy that it would take"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 106260.0,
      "end_time": 108260.0,
      "text": "for eight billion people living in cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 108260.0,
      "end_time": 110260.0,
      "text": "that are even somewhat like the cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 110260.0,
      "end_time": 112260.0,
      "text": "that those of us in the global North live in today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 112260.0,
      "end_time": 114260.0,
      "text": "we would have to generate"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 114260.0,
      "end_time": 116260.0,
      "text": "an absolutely astonishing amount of energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 116260.0,
      "end_time": 118260.0,
      "text": "It may be possible"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 118260.0,
      "end_time": 120260.0,
      "text": "that we are not even able"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 120260.0,
      "end_time": 123260.0,
      "text": "to build that much clean energy."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 123260.0,
      "end_time": 126260.0,
      "text": "So if we&#39;re seriously talking about tackling climate change"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 126260.0,
      "end_time": 128259.0,
      "text": "on an urbanizing planet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 128258.99999999999,
      "end_time": 131260.0,
      "text": "we need to look somewhere else for the solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 131260.0,
      "end_time": 134260.0,
      "text": "The solution, in fact, may be closer to hand than we think,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 134260.0,
      "end_time": 136260.0,
      "text": "because all of those cities we&#39;re building"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 136260.0,
      "end_time": 138260.0,
      "text": "are opportunities."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 138260.0,
      "end_time": 141260.0,
      "text": "Every city determines to a very large extent"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 141260.0,
      "end_time": 144260.0,
      "text": "the amount of energy used by its inhabitants."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 144260.0,
      "end_time": 147260.0,
      "text": "We tend to think of energy use as a behavioral thing --"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 147260.0,
      "end_time": 149260.0,
      "text": "I choose to turn this light switch on --"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 149260.0,
      "end_time": 152260.0,
      "text": "but really, enormous amounts of our energy use"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 152260.0,
      "end_time": 154260.0,
      "text": "are predestined"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 154260.0,
      "end_time": 157260.0,
      "text": "by the kinds of communities and cities that we live in."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 157260.0,
      "end_time": 159260.0,
      "text": "I won&#39;t show you very many graphs today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 159260.0,
      "end_time": 162260.0,
      "text": "but if I can just focus on this one for a moment,"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 162260.0,
      "end_time": 164260.0,
      "text": "it really tells us a lot of what we need to know --"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 164260.0,
      "end_time": 166260.0,
      "text": "which is, quite simply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 166260.0,
      "end_time": 168260.0,
      "text": "that if you look, for example, at transportation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 168260.0,
      "end_time": 170260.0,
      "text": "a major category of climate emissions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 170260.0,
      "end_time": 172260.0,
      "text": "there is a direct relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 172260.0,
      "end_time": 174260.0,
      "text": "between how dense a city is"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 174260.0,
      "end_time": 176260.0,
      "text": "and the amount of climate emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 176260.0,
      "end_time": 179260.0,
      "text": "that its residents spew out into the air."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 179260.0,
      "end_time": 181260.0,
      "text": "And the correlation, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 181260.0,
      "end_time": 184260.0,
      "text": "is that denser places tend to have lower emissions --"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 184260.0,
      "end_time": 187260.0,
      "text": "which isn&#39;t really all that difficult to figure out, if you think about it."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 187260.0,
      "end_time": 189260.0,
      "text": "Basically,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 189260.0,
      "end_time": 192260.0,
      "text": "we substitute, in our lives,"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 192260.0,
      "end_time": 194260.0,
      "text": "access to the things we want."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 194260.0,
      "end_time": 196260.0,
      "text": "We go out there and we hop in our cars"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 196260.0,
      "end_time": 198260.0,
      "text": "and we drive from place to place."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 198260.0,
      "end_time": 201260.0,
      "text": "And we&#39;re basically using mobility to get the access we need."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 201260.0,
      "end_time": 203260.0,
      "text": "But when we live in a denser community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 203260.0,
      "end_time": 205260.0,
      "text": "suddenly what we find, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 205260.0,
      "end_time": 207260.0,
      "text": "is that the things we need are close by."
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 207260.0,
      "end_time": 209260.0,
      "text": "And since the most sustainable trip"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 209260.0,
      "end_time": 212260.0,
      "text": "is the one that you never had to make in the first place,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 212260.0,
      "end_time": 215260.0,
      "text": "suddenly our lives become instantly more sustainable."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 215260.0,
      "end_time": 217260.0,
      "text": "And it is possible, of course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 217260.0,
      "end_time": 220260.0,
      "text": "to increase the density of the communities around us."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 220260.0,
      "end_time": 222260.0,
      "text": "Some places are doing this with new eco districts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 222260.0,
      "end_time": 224260.0,
      "text": "developing whole new sustainable neighborhoods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 224260.0,
      "end_time": 226260.0,
      "text": "which is nice work if you can get it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 226260.0,
      "end_time": 229260.0,
      "text": "but most of the time, what we&#39;re talking about is, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 229260.0,
      "end_time": 231260.0,
      "text": "reweaving the urban fabric that we already have."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 231260.0,
      "end_time": 234260.0,
      "text": "So we&#39;re talking about things like infill development:"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 234260.0,
      "end_time": 236260.0,
      "text": "really sharp little changes"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 236260.0,
      "end_time": 238260.0,
      "text": "to where we have buildings, where we&#39;re developing."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 238260.0,
      "end_time": 240260.0,
      "text": "Urban retrofitting:"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 240260.0,
      "end_time": 242260.0,
      "text": "creating different sorts of spaces and uses"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 242260.0,
      "end_time": 244260.0,
      "text": "out of places that are already there."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 244260.0,
      "end_time": 246260.0,
      "text": "Increasingly, we&#39;re realizing"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 246260.0,
      "end_time": 249260.0,
      "text": "that we don&#39;t even need to densify an entire city."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 249260.0,
      "end_time": 252260.0,
      "text": "What we need instead is an average density"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 252260.0,
      "end_time": 254260.0,
      "text": "that rises to a level"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 254260.0,
      "end_time": 256260.0,
      "text": "where we don&#39;t drive as much and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 256260.0,
      "end_time": 258260.0,
      "text": "And that can be done"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 258260.0,
      "end_time": 261260.0,
      "text": "by raising the density in very specific spots a whole lot."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 261260.0,
      "end_time": 264260.0,
      "text": "So you can think of it as tent poles"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 264260.0,
      "end_time": 267260.0,
      "text": "that actually raise the density of the entire city."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 267260.0,
      "end_time": 269260.0,
      "text": "And we find that when we do that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 269260.0,
      "end_time": 271260.0,
      "text": "we can, in fact, have a few places that are really hyper-dense"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 271260.0,
      "end_time": 273260.0,
      "text": "within a wider fabric of places"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 273260.0,
      "end_time": 275260.0,
      "text": "that are perhaps a little more comfortable"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 275260.0,
      "end_time": 277260.0,
      "text": "and achieve the same results."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 277260.0,
      "end_time": 280260.0,
      "text": "Now we may find that there are places that are really, really dense"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 280260.0,
      "end_time": 282260.0,
      "text": "and still hold onto their cars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 282260.0,
      "end_time": 285260.0,
      "text": "but the reality is that, by and large,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 285260.0,
      "end_time": 288260.0,
      "text": "what we see when we get a lot of people together with the right conditions"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 288260.0,
      "end_time": 290260.0,
      "text": "is a threshold effect,"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 290260.0,
      "end_time": 292260.0,
      "text": "where people simply stop driving as much,"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 292260.0,
      "end_time": 294260.0,
      "text": "and increasingly, more and more people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 294260.0,
      "end_time": 296260.0,
      "text": "if they&#39;re surrounded by places that make them feel at home,"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 296260.0,
      "end_time": 298260.0,
      "text": "give up their cars altogether."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 298260.0,
      "end_time": 301260.0,
      "text": "And this is a huge, huge energy savings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 301260.0,
      "end_time": 303260.0,
      "text": "because what comes out of our tailpipe"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 303260.0,
      "end_time": 305260.0,
      "text": "is really just the beginning of the story"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 305260.0,
      "end_time": 307260.0,
      "text": "with climate emissions from cars."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 307260.0,
      "end_time": 309260.0,
      "text": "We have the manufacture of the car, the disposal of the car,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 309260.0,
      "end_time": 312260.0,
      "text": "all of the parking and freeways and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 312260.0,
      "end_time": 314260.0,
      "text": "When you can get rid of all of those"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 314260.0,
      "end_time": 316260.0,
      "text": "because somebody doesn&#39;t use any of them really,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 316260.0,
      "end_time": 318260.0,
      "text": "you find that you can actually cut transportation emissions"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 318260.0,
      "end_time": 320260.0,
      "text": "as much as 90 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 320260.0,
      "end_time": 322260.0,
      "text": "And people are embracing this."
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 322260.0,
      "end_time": 325260.0,
      "text": "All around the world, we&#39;re seeing more and more people embrace this walkshed life."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 325260.0,
      "end_time": 328260.0,
      "text": "People are saying that it&#39;s moving from the idea of the dream home"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 328260.0,
      "end_time": 330260.0,
      "text": "to the dream neighborhood."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 330260.0,
      "end_time": 332260.0,
      "text": "And when you layer that over"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 332260.0,
      "end_time": 335260.0,
      "text": "with the kind of ubiquitous communications that we&#39;re starting to see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 335260.0,
      "end_time": 337260.0,
      "text": "what you find is, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 337260.0,
      "end_time": 340260.0,
      "text": "even more access suffused into spaces."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 340260.0,
      "end_time": 342260.0,
      "text": "Some of it&#39;s transportation access."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 342260.0,
      "end_time": 345260.0,
      "text": "This is a Mapnificent map that shows me, in this case,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 345260.0,
      "end_time": 347260.0,
      "text": "how far I can get from my home in 30 minutes"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 347260.0,
      "end_time": 349260.0,
      "text": "using public transportation."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 349260.0,
      "end_time": 351260.0,
      "text": "Some of it is about walking. It&#39;s not all perfect yet."
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 351260.0,
      "end_time": 353260.0,
      "text": "This is Google Walking Maps."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 353260.0,
      "end_time": 355260.0,
      "text": "I asked how to do the greater Ridgeway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 355260.0,
      "end_time": 357260.0,
      "text": "and it told me to go via Guernsey."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 357260.0,
      "end_time": 359260.0,
      "text": "It did tell me that this route"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 359260.0,
      "end_time": 361260.0,
      "text": "maybe missing sidewalks or pedestrian paths, though."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 361260.0,
      "end_time": 363260.0,
      "text": "(Laughter)"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 363260.0,
      "end_time": 365260.0,
      "text": "But the technologies are getting better,"
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 365260.0,
      "end_time": 367260.0,
      "text": "and we&#39;re starting to really kind of crowdsource this navigation."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 367260.0,
      "end_time": 369260.0,
      "text": "And as we just heard earlier,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 369260.0,
      "end_time": 372260.0,
      "text": "of course, we&#39;re also learning how to put information on dumb objects."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 372260.0,
      "end_time": 374260.0,
      "text": "Things that don&#39;t have any wiring in them at all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 374260.0,
      "end_time": 376260.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re learning how to include"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 376260.0,
      "end_time": 379260.0,
      "text": "in these systems of notation and navigation."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 379260.0,
      "end_time": 381260.0,
      "text": "Part of what we&#39;re finding with this"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 381260.0,
      "end_time": 383260.0,
      "text": "is that what we thought"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 383260.0,
      "end_time": 385260.0,
      "text": "was the major point"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 385260.0,
      "end_time": 388260.0,
      "text": "of manufacturing and consumption,"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 388260.0,
      "end_time": 390260.0,
      "text": "which is to get a bunch of stuff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 390260.0,
      "end_time": 392260.0,
      "text": "is not, in fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 392260.0,
      "end_time": 394260.0,
      "text": "how we really live best in dense environments."
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 394260.0,
      "end_time": 396260.0,
      "text": "What we&#39;re finding is that what we want"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 396260.0,
      "end_time": 398260.0,
      "text": "is access to the capacities of things."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 398260.0,
      "end_time": 401260.0,
      "text": "My favorite example is a drill. Who here owns a drill, a home power drill?"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 401260.0,
      "end_time": 403260.0,
      "text": "Okay. I do too."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 403260.0,
      "end_time": 405260.0,
      "text": "The average home power drill is used somewhere between six and 20 minutes"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 405260.0,
      "end_time": 407260.0,
      "text": "in its entire lifetime,"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 407260.0,
      "end_time": 409260.0,
      "text": "depending on who you ask."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 409260.0,
      "end_time": 412260.0,
      "text": "And so what we do is we buy these drills"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 412260.0,
      "end_time": 415260.0,
      "text": "that have a potential capacity of thousands of hours of drill time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 415260.0,
      "end_time": 418260.0,
      "text": "use them once or twice to put a hole in the wall and let them sit."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 418260.0,
      "end_time": 420260.0,
      "text": "Our cities, I would put to you,"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 420260.0,
      "end_time": 423260.0,
      "text": "are stockpiles of these surplus capacities."
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 423260.0,
      "end_time": 425260.0,
      "text": "And while we could try and figure out"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 425260.0,
      "end_time": 427260.0,
      "text": "new ways to use those capacities --"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 427260.0,
      "end_time": 429260.0,
      "text": "such as cooking or making ice sculptures"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 429260.0,
      "end_time": 431260.0,
      "text": "or even a mafia hit --"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 431260.0,
      "end_time": 433260.0,
      "text": "what we probably will find"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 433260.0,
      "end_time": 435260.0,
      "text": "is that, in fact, turning those products into services"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 435260.0,
      "end_time": 437260.0,
      "text": "that we have access to when we want them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 437260.0,
      "end_time": 440260.0,
      "text": "is a far smarter way to go."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 440260.0,
      "end_time": 443260.0,
      "text": "And in fact, even space itself is turning into a service."
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 443260.0,
      "end_time": 445260.0,
      "text": "We&#39;re finding that people can share the same spaces,"
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 445260.0,
      "end_time": 448260.0,
      "text": "do stuff with vacant space."
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 448260.0,
      "end_time": 450260.0,
      "text": "Buildings are becoming bundles of services."
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 450260.0,
      "end_time": 452260.0,
      "text": "So we have new designs"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 452260.0,
      "end_time": 455260.0,
      "text": "that are helping us take mechanical things that we used to spend energy on --"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 455260.0,
      "end_time": 457260.0,
      "text": "like heating, cooling etc. --"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 457260.0,
      "end_time": 460260.0,
      "text": "and turn them into things that we avoid spending energy on."
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 460260.0,
      "end_time": 462260.0,
      "text": "So we light our buildings with daylight."
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 462260.0,
      "end_time": 465260.0,
      "text": "We cool them with breezes. We heat them with sunshine."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 465260.0,
      "end_time": 467260.0,
      "text": "In fact, when we use all these things,"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 467260.0,
      "end_time": 469260.0,
      "text": "what we&#39;ve found is that, in some cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 469260.0,
      "end_time": 471260.0,
      "text": "energy use in a building can drop as much as 90 percent."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 471260.0,
      "end_time": 473260.0,
      "text": "Which brings on another threshold effect"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 473260.0,
      "end_time": 475260.0,
      "text": "I like to call furnace dumping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 475260.0,
      "end_time": 477260.0,
      "text": "which is, quite simply,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 477260.0,
      "end_time": 479260.0,
      "text": "if you have a building that doesn&#39;t need to be heated with a furnace,"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 479260.0,
      "end_time": 481260.0,
      "text": "you save a whole bunch of money up front."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 481260.0,
      "end_time": 483260.0,
      "text": "These things actually become cheaper to build"
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 483260.0,
      "end_time": 485260.0,
      "text": "than the alternatives."
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 485260.0,
      "end_time": 488260.0,
      "text": "Now when we look at being able"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 488260.0,
      "end_time": 491260.0,
      "text": "to slash our product use, slash our transportation use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 491260.0,
      "end_time": 493260.0,
      "text": "slash our building energy use,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 493260.0,
      "end_time": 496260.0,
      "text": "all of that is great, but it still leaves something behind."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 496260.0,
      "end_time": 498260.0,
      "text": "And if we&#39;re going to really, truly become sustainable cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 498260.0,
      "end_time": 500260.0,
      "text": "we need to think a little differently."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 500260.0,
      "end_time": 502260.0,
      "text": "This is one way to do it."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 502260.0,
      "end_time": 504260.0,
      "text": "This is Vancouver&#39;s propaganda about how green a city they are."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 504260.0,
      "end_time": 506260.0,
      "text": "And certainly lots of people have taken to heart"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 506260.0,
      "end_time": 509260.0,
      "text": "this idea that a sustainable city is covered in greenery."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 509260.0,
      "end_time": 511260.0,
      "text": "So we have visions like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 511260.0,
      "end_time": 514260.0,
      "text": "We have visions like this. We have visions like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 514260.0,
      "end_time": 516260.0,
      "text": "Now all of these are fine projects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 516260.0,
      "end_time": 519260.0,
      "text": "but they really have missed an essential point,"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 519260.0,
      "end_time": 521260.0,
      "text": "which is it&#39;s not about the leaves above,"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 521260.0,
      "end_time": 523260.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s about the systems below."
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 523260.0,
      "end_time": 525260.0,
      "text": "Do they, for instance, capture rainwater"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 525260.0,
      "end_time": 527260.0,
      "text": "so that we can reduce water use?"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 527260.0,
      "end_time": 530260.0,
      "text": "Water is energy intensive."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 530260.0,
      "end_time": 532260.0,
      "text": "Do they, perhaps, include green infrastructure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 532260.0,
      "end_time": 534260.0,
      "text": "so that we can take runoff"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 534260.0,
      "end_time": 536260.0,
      "text": "and water that&#39;s going out of our houses"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 536260.0,
      "end_time": 538260.0,
      "text": "and clean it and filter it"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 538260.0,
      "end_time": 540260.0,
      "text": "and grow urban street trees?"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 540260.0,
      "end_time": 543260.0,
      "text": "Do they connect us back to the ecosystems around us"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 543260.0,
      "end_time": 545260.0,
      "text": "by, for example, connecting us to rivers"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 545260.0,
      "end_time": 547260.0,
      "text": "and allowing for restoration?"
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 547260.0,
      "end_time": 549260.0,
      "text": "Do they allow for pollination,"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 549260.0,
      "end_time": 551260.0,
      "text": "pollinator pathways"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 551260.0,
      "end_time": 554260.0,
      "text": "that bees and butterflies and such can come back into our cities?"
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 554260.0,
      "end_time": 556260.0,
      "text": "Do they even take the very waste matter"
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 556260.0,
      "end_time": 559260.0,
      "text": "that we have from food and fiber and so forth,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 559260.0,
      "end_time": 561260.0,
      "text": "and turn it back into soil"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 561260.0,
      "end_time": 563260.0,
      "text": "and sequester carbon --"
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 563260.0,
      "end_time": 565260.0,
      "text": "take carbon out of the air"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 565260.0,
      "end_time": 567260.0,
      "text": "in the process of using our cities?"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 567260.0,
      "end_time": 570260.0,
      "text": "I would submit to you that all of these things are not only possible,"
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 570260.0,
      "end_time": 572260.0,
      "text": "they&#39;re being done right now,"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 572260.0,
      "end_time": 574260.0,
      "text": "and that it&#39;s a darn good thing."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 574260.0,
      "end_time": 577260.0,
      "text": "Because right now, our economy by and large"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 577260.0,
      "end_time": 579260.0,
      "text": "operates as Paul Hawken said,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 579260.0,
      "end_time": 581260.0,
      "text": "\"by stealing the future, selling it in the present"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 581260.0,
      "end_time": 583260.0,
      "text": "and calling it GDP.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 583260.0,
      "end_time": 585260.0,
      "text": "And if we have another eight billion"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 585260.0,
      "end_time": 587260.0,
      "text": "or seven billion,"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 587260.0,
      "end_time": 589260.0,
      "text": "or six billion, even, people,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 589260.0,
      "end_time": 592260.0,
      "text": "living on a planet where their cities also steal the future,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 592260.0,
      "end_time": 594260.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re going to run out of future really fast."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 594260.0,
      "end_time": 596260.0,
      "text": "But if we think differently,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 596260.0,
      "end_time": 598260.0,
      "text": "I think that, in fact, we can have cities"
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 598260.0,
      "end_time": 600260.0,
      "text": "that are not only zero emissions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 600260.0,
      "end_time": 602260.0,
      "text": "but have unlimited possibilities as well."
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 602260.0,
      "end_time": 604260.0,
      "text": "Thank you very much."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 604260.0,
      "end_time": 607260.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}